  "prompt": "How do you start a company?",
  "response": "Starting a company involves several key steps:\n\n1. Develop a business idea\n- Identify a market need\n- Research your potential market\n- Define your product or service\n\n2. Create a business plan\n- Outline your business strategy\n- Define target market\n- Project financials\n- Set goals and milestones\n\n3. Choose a business structure\n- Sole proprietorship\n- Partnership\n- Limited Liability Company (LLC)\n- Corporation\n\n4. Register your business\n- Choose a business name\n- Register with state/local government\n- Obtain necessary licenses and permits\n\n5. Secure funding\n- Personal savings\n- Loans\n- Investors\n- Crowdfunding\n- Grants\n\n6. Set up business finances\n- Open a business bank account\n- Set up accounting systems\n- Obtain business credit cards\n\n7. Build your team\n- Hire employees or contractors\n- Define roles and responsibilities\n\n8. Develop your product/service\n- Create prototypes\n- Test and refine\n\n9. Market your business\n- Build a website\n- Use social media\n- Network\n- Develop marketing strategy\n\n10. Launch and grow\n- Start selling\n- Track performance\n- Continuously improve\n\nEach step requires careful planning and execution.",
